        {
            "user_id": "user_010",
            "rating": 5,
            "content": "I have bought too many backpacks for my own good. This is the one I now use for travel. It's lightweight, quite comfortable, and has just enough space for a minimalist travel wardrobe.<br><br>I have to say: it's quite hard to find backpacks with hip belts! I think any backpack above 20L should have hip belts, and maybe even the 20L ones should have mount points to attach one if needed. There are those of us who carry heavy things and would really appreciate the weight transfer from a hip belt.<br><br>I also appreciate that this backpack fits my Asian female torso length. I saw a video review by a Caucasian man saying the 35L was too short for him, and that's what convinced me to order this. <br><br>Thank you, Decathlon, for designing and selling backpacks like this. I know you're not specifically a travel company, but your camping and hiking gear are great for travel too. I don't hike up mountains but I do walk on Asian sidewalks (not the greatest) and climb stairs. Being able to do so with affordable, comfortable gear has made me a Decathlon loyalist for life."
        },
        {
